      <h2>Posts</h2>
      <p>Posts live in <code>posts</code> by default, but you can use a
      different directory for posts with the <code>-p</code> flag or by setting
      the <code>posts</code> variable in your .cobalt.yml.</p>
      <p>Example:</p>
      <pre><code>
extends: posts.liquid

title:   My first Blogpost
date:    01 Jan 2016 21:00:00 +0100
---
Hey there this is my first blogpost and this is super awesome.

My Blog is lorem ipsum like, yes it is..
</code></pre>
      <p>The content before <code>---</code> are meta attributes ("front
      matter") made accessible to the template via their key (see below).</p>
      <p>The <code>extends</code> attribute specifies which layout will be
      used.</p>
      <p>The <code>date</code> attribute will be used to sort blog posts (from
      last to
      first). <code>date</code> must have the format <code>%dd %Mon %YYYY
        %HH:%MM:%SS %zzzz</code>, so for
      example <code>27 May 2016 21:00:30 +0100</code>.</p>
      <h3>Drafts</h3>
      <p>Cobalt supports leaving posts in "draft" state. Drafts will not be
      rendered unless Cobalt is run with the <code>--drafts</code> flag.</p>
      <p>To mark a post as draft you can either set draft: true in your front
      matter or add it to the drafts folder (_drafts by default). The draft
      folder location can be specified using the draft key in your
      .cobalt.yml.</p>
